  "text": "The provision and management of services by public service media is an \"ethical imperative\" when associated to fundamental rights and freedoms [CITATION_1] . This is the golden age of television (EBU, 2014) , as more than 9,000 channels through various platforms (OBS, 2016) are consumed daily by 87% of Europeans (CE, 2013) . Nevertheless, the universal role of Public Service Media is contested within and increasingly complex digital arena.",
